pageContext.claim: “The New York Times would be dead right now [if it weren't for me]. The Washington Post would be out of business. I hate to say it but cable television would be -- it's obsolete. Cable would be out of business, so we'll go another, hopefully, five years and we'll keep everybody happy.”
pageContext.analysis: The New York Times has been consistently profitable for the past ten years, so Trump is simply making up this claim.
